{"id":"hep-th/9110010","submitter":"Tim Hollowood","authors":"Timothy Hollowood","title":"Quantum Solitons in Affine Toda Field Theories","comments":"21 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1016/0550-3213(92)90579-Z","report-no":null,"categories":"hep-th","license":null,"abstract":"  The spectra of $A_r$ affine Toda field theories with imaginary coupling\nconstant, are investigated. Soliton solutions are found, which, despite the\nnon-unitary form of the Lagrangian, have real classical masses and are stable\nto small perturbations. The quantum corrections to the soliton masses are\ndetermined, to lowest order in $\\hbar$. The solitons have the same spectrum as\nthe fundamental Toda particles; a feature that is preserved in the quantum\ntheory.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 3 Oct 1991 04:59:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-10-22"}
